                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17150223-27-off136 t17150223-27-crimeloc140"></join>, where the deceas'd came up to him and drew his Sword, swearing he would stab him to the Heart if he did not draw; and that thereupon he did draw in his own Defence, and the deceas'd received the Wound. There were several who swore the deceas'd was a very quarrelsome Fellow, and had wounded several People; and that the Prisoner was one of a quite contrary Character, whereupon he was found <rs id="t17150223-27-verdict141" type="verdictDescription">
